author: Joe Buczek
title: Reed City tops Big Rapids in " OT on the Road"
text:
Reed City tops Big Rapids in " OT on the Road" Posted: JoeBuczek@9and10news.com 
BIG RAPIDS – Reed City continued its unbeaten start to the season and qualified for the playoffs with a 22-7 win over Big Rapids on Friday in our “Overtime on the Road” matchup. 
“A tough fought game by both groups,” Reed City coach Monty Price said. “Coach Seltzer is doing a heck of a job turning the Big Rapids program around. Our kids fought through a lot of adversity tonight and they had to overcome a lot of things that went wrong for us in the game…We come out on top, and I'm very proud of my kids.” 
The Coyotes host Central Montcalm next Friday, while the Cardinals (4-2) travel to Chippewa Hills (5-1). Most Popular Stories Most Popular Stories More>>
